What is Intravesical Hyperthermia?

Intravesical Hyperthermia is a non‑invasive physical therapy applied directly within the bladder. It delivers high temperature-typically via radio‑frequency or microwave energy-through physiological cavities such as the urethra to induce biological effects that damage tumor or inflammatory cells while preserving surrounding healthy tissue.

